The paper deals with the analysis of online greedy matching algorithms on random bipartite graphs, which involves topics such as graph theory, optimization, and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely sub-categories. The use of differential equations to describe the evolution of the matching process suggests a connection to numerical analysis and scientific computing, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the study of performance ratios and asymptotic analysis may also relate to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
